Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
26 Ipswich Street is a modern mixed-use development consisting of multiple commercial units across three buildings suitable for office, retail and light industrial use.  Building 3 offers great exposure, located on one of Fyshwick's main roads with excellent street frontage.  Suites can be offered as a conditioned space or full turn key solutions are available.  This units are ideal for any occupier with strict security requirements.  Visitor parking is available on site as well as undercroft for tenants.

The buildings offer a variety of inclusions such as:
• Bi-fold doors to allow for access for deliveries
• Mezzanine space ranging in size
• Quality office space with excellent natural light
• Double glazed windows
• High ceilings

Building 3 Availability:

Unit 13:  460sqm* ground floor suite with high ceiling and can be offered as a warm shell with ceiling, lighting and airconditioning or turn key offering to meet requirements.  Signage options available.

The development features include:
• Compliance with the BCA and the new mobility and disability code
• Base building complete - ready for fit out
• Opportunity to customize and integrate warm shell fit out
• 200+ carparks, surface and secure basement
• High profile street location, conveniently opposite a self-storage facility
• High Ground floor clearance, 4 metres floor to floor
• Siphonic roof stormwater system
• 60,000 litre stormwater retention tanks for reuse in toilets and landscaping
• 150mm commercial grade aluminium window systems - ASIO T4 compliant
• 3 phase power - upgradable
• Viridian Double-glazed windows and doors toughened eco glass both sides
• Natural light throughout all tenancies
• Insulated basements for ground floor tenancies
• Heavy loading concrete suspended slabs designed to take compactus and storage loads, (ground floor 10kpa, first floor 6kpa)
• 30 bicycle parks
• Excellent accessibility to public transport, bicycle and walking paths

If you require more information, please contact CBRE.

*Approx.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Box Business Centre is a high quality and architecturally designed development located in the busy industrial suburb of Fyshwick. This development is compromised 16 individual self-contained business units, and allocated parking.  On site burger shop provides amenity for tenants which is also available in abundance around the development.

High profile tenant mix including a range of business types.

Available for lease are units of 270sqm* and 350sqm*.

For further information or to arrange an inspection please contact CBRE.

*Approx.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: MODERN BOUTIQUE MIXED USE DEVELOPMENT - READY TO OCCUPY

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
24-26 Mort Street is located within one of Canberra's most popular and vibrant precincts. The property is situated in a fantastic location surrounded by various commercial offices, some of Canberra's best retailers, restaurants, cafes, residential apartments and Hotels. The Canberra Center is a short walk away as well as the City Bus Interchange.  The property boasts a wide permitted use making it suitable for a broad range of operators including but not limited to:

- Retailers
- Service providers
- Food operators
- Health practitioners/Medical operators

The building has undergone extensive works and will shortly commence internal upgrades. A new lift will be installed to service the first floor tenancies and plans are underway to activate the lane way between the two buildings.

Strong public transport links are available with a bus stop situated directly in front of the building as well as public visitor car parking. The future light rail stops are a short walk away. Ample onsite reserved parking is available.

Available for Lease:

102sqm*- Frontage onto Mort Street 

The flexible floor plate allows the space to be altered to meet various businesses requirements.  Each unit has provision for grease trap, sewer and plumbing.

For further information on this exciting opportunity please contact CBRE.

*Approx.
